(44, 11, 28, 11, 17, 1, 16, 'great dearth throughout all the world', 'Connection of Dearth and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize a time of great dearth and the miraculous provision of sustenance. In Acts, Agabus foretells a famine, while in 1 Kings, Elijah experiences a drought but is sustained by God through a widow''s limited resources.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
